        "body": "﻿## Summary\n- Improve Indonesian Control UI copy that was still English in the Agents, Debug, and exec approval panels.\n- Keep placeholders unchanged for translated strings.\n- Add a changelog entry for the user-facing locale fix.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`\n- `pnpm format:check ui/src/i18n/locales/id.ts CHANGELOG.md`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- Imported `ui/src/i18n/locales/id.ts` with `node --import tsx --input-type=module` and checked representative translated keys.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Indonesian users still saw several English Control UI labels in the Agents, Debug, and exec approval panels.\n- Real environment tested: Windows checkout of this branch after the patch, with dependencies installed by pnpm.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: ran `node --import tsx --input-type=module -e \"import { id } from './ui/src/i18n/locales/id.ts'; ...\"` from the repository root to load the shipped Indonesian locale module used by Control UI.\n- Evidence after fix: copied terminal output from the local run:\n\n```text\nagents.noAgents=Tidak ada agen\nagents.selectTitle=Pilih agen\nagents.channels.empty=Tidak ada saluran ditemukan.\nagents.files.emptyDraft=Draf kosong\ndebug.security.audit=Audit keamanan\nexecApproval.allowOnce=Izinkan sekali\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: the Indonesian locale module now returns Indonesian labels for the representative Agents, Debug, and exec approval keys instead of the previous English text.\n- What was not tested: no live browser screenshot was captured. The full `node --import tsx scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts check --locale id` check is currently blocked by unrelated raw-copy baseline drift in `ui/src/ui/views/config-quick.ts` (`Browser enabled`, `Tool profile`).\n\nAI-assisted: yes.",
